label sacrifice:

    scene black
    with None
    
    play music "lowhum.mp3" fadein 3.0

    "{cps=2} {/cps}.{cps=2} {/cps}.{cps=2} {/cps}.{cps=2} {/cps}"

    "Astrid lived to serve."

    "Every step forward, every strike, every monster led to their doom, every breath she has ever taken..."

    "All of it was to enact the will of her dear, loving, matriarch."

    "So of course, when She had entrusted her and her alone to capture the vampire who had been terrorizing her small village, she practically leapt at the opportunity."

    "She should've known it was never going to be that easy. Things in her life hardly ever panned out that way."

    "Instead of a quick and easy operation, her new routine became something like this:"


    scene sacrifice_1
    with dissolve

    "1.) Come back empty-handed day after day, missing the wretch by the skin of her teeth."

    "2.) Walk down the stone paths to the Highmother's throne, head low and hidden in her hood as passersby looked upon her with disgust. Feel the shame sinking deep into her skin."

    scene sacrifice_2
    "3.) Try to hold back tears as the Highmother chastises her for the ruin she brought upon the village. "

    "Upon her own existence."

    scene sacrifice_3
    "4.) Remind herself of the love and mercy that She had shown her before. Think about Her soft hands running through her hair, beckoning Her sweet girl closer."

    "Think about the times She had looked upon her as She would any other child, and remember how it felt to be her without sin."

    "Without blame."

    scene black
    "5.) Know that those days are long gone. Memories rationed to keep her hunger sated on late nights."

    "Finally, "

    "Know that all of this is her fault."

    scene sacrifice_4
    "And just like that, she was gone."

    "Like a bat out of hell, she flies, with only a briefly biting gust of wind left in her wake as a sign she was ever there in the first place."

    "As the full moon glows ever brighter, Jun Yue disappears into the night sky."

    scene black
    "Turning her attention back to the ground, Astrid's blood runs cold."

    "She didn't know what she expected to happen. "

    "Panic, maybe? Outrage?"

    "The streets stirring, people rousing from a sleepy haze.."

    "Screams, chatter, clamor-"

    "Anything but this. "

    "A thick and oppressive silence, uninterrupted by the usual hymns and chants."

    "Eerily expectant. Waiting."

    "Head spinning, Astrid wonders what for."

    "She doesn't wonder for very long."

    scene sacrifice_5
    "Eyes previously fixated on the captive vampire now rest squarely on her. Unbothered. The perfect image of calm and tranquility. "

    "From behind her, the guards begin to mobilize, blocking off any viable routes for escape."

    scene sacrifice_6
    "When she remains as still as a statue, one of them breaks from the line, impatiently prodding her with the butt of his spear."

    scene sacrifice_7
    "GUARD : Move. "

    scene black
    "Ah. "

    "Now she understood."

    "Yes, Jun was gone, but the ritual still needed to be complete."

    "It would happen tonight, regardless of which monster's blood stained the executioner's blade."

    "Vampire or werewolf, it didn't matter. All were scourges to the common good."

    "No amount of penance could ever outweigh the gravity of her sin."

    "It was always going to come to this."

    scene sacrifice_8
    "Her destiny is clear now, beckoning to her with outstretched arms. Every affliction has its remedy. "

    "Of course, she obeys."

    "She walks down the rocky path, a dog led on a leash wrapped tight around her neck. The crowd's eyes follow her. "

    "Silence envelopes the square, the only sound that cuts through is the trudge of her boots."

    "The large stone platform stands just a few steps away. Moss and grass grows around its base."

    "In the past, she's seen countless monsters lead to this very spot. She's seen them struggle, fight… do anything and everything to resist what is best for them."

    "But not her. She would be different."

    "She would be their messiah. "

    "The pastor's favorite little lamb, sitting still and pretty on the pedestal, waiting for the knife to draw out of its sheath. "

    "She would not squirm, would not bleat as the blade met its mark. "

    "And when it was all set and done, and her blood drip, drip, dripped onto the ground beneath her.."

    "..she would finally be clean."

    scene sacrifice_9
    "Astrid had lived to serve."

    stop music fadeout 2.0
    "Now, she would die to serve."

    $ persistent.epilogue = True

    return

